The White House is set to unveil the National HIV/AIDS Strategy (NHAS) on July 13, 2010. The plan aims to reduce HIV infections, improve access to care for those living with HIV, and address health disparities related to HIV. The NHAS will provide guidance for policymakers, prevention partners, and the public on how the United States can lower HIV incidence, improve care for those with HIV, and reduce health disparities. The event will be attended by Health and Human Services Secretary Kathleen Sebelius, White House Domestic Policy Council Director Melody Barnes, Office of National AIDS Policy Director Jeffrey Crowley, and HHS Assistant Secretary for Health Dr. Howard Koh. Media wishing to attend must RSVP by July 12.